Didn't I ask you to look after him?

57
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:34,260
I...

58
00:02:34,980 --> 00:02:37,030
Brother Wen Chang, it's your turn.

59
00:02:37,030 --> 00:02:38,320
Wake up, Brother Wen Chang!

60
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:40,510
Brother Yue,

61
00:02:41,110 --> 00:02:43,200
since Du Fu is here,

62
00:02:43,570 --> 00:02:45,330
I should not embarrass myself
with my mediocre poem.

63
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:47,940
I should

64
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:49,480
go home.

65
00:02:51,540 --> 00:02:52,770
I should go back!

66
00:02:54,380 --> 00:02:56,390
All right, the poetry party
has officially begun.

67
00:02:56,900 --> 00:02:58,220
I'm willing to be the first

68
00:02:58,220 --> 00:02:59,180
in hope of inspiring others.

69
00:02:59,910 --> 00:03:01,180
Which one of you

70
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:03,180
would like to come up
and compete with me?

71
00:03:03,410 --> 00:03:04,760
We can't let Yu Wen Bai win.

72
00:03:05,190 --> 00:03:05,620
You...

73
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:06,690
Look after him closely, all right?

74
00:03:08,940 --> 00:03:09,390
I'll do it.

75
00:03:13,140 --> 00:03:15,170
This young man looks handsome.

76
00:03:15,170 --> 00:03:16,610
Yeah, he looks pretty.

77
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,300
What's she doing up there?

78
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,640
How do I address you, Sir?

79
00:03:21,220 --> 00:03:21,890
Yue Chuan.

80
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:23,660
Oh, it's Brother Yue.

81
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:25,700
The rules of this poetry competition

82
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:27,710
are very simple. Best of three games.

83
00:03:28,050 --> 00:03:29,300
You and I take turns to ask questions.

84
00:03:29,450 --> 00:03:31,840
We will write our own poems,

85
00:03:32,220 --> 00:03:33,930
and the audience will be the judge.

86
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:34,800
What do you think?

87
00:03:34,950 --> 00:03:36,530
Fine. You first.

88
00:03:37,210 --> 00:03:37,860
Great!

89
00:03:39,350 --> 00:03:40,390
The first round

90
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:41,730
concerns the frontier fortress.

91
00:03:42,650 --> 00:03:43,860
I already have mine in mind.

92
00:03:44,330 --> 00:03:45,690
Brother Yue, feel free
to spend some time

93
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:47,250
to think of your poem.

94
00:03:48,220 --> 00:03:49,630
No need. I'm ready.

95
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:52,530
The muddy lakeside road now lies
chapped amid winds of extreme freeze.

96
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:55,020
Their branches broken, the parasol trees
stripped of their withered leaves.

97
00:03:56,130 --> 00:03:58,460
Though the armor is torn
in constant desert wars,

98
00:03:58,850 --> 00:04:01,470
a red flag is all one sees,
marching up the snow-capped peak.

99
00:04:02,850 --> 00:04:03,250
You...

100
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:04,560
Great!

101
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,890
What a great poem!

102
00:04:05,890 --> 00:04:07,280
What's going on?

103
00:04:07,430 --> 00:04:09,150
Wow, he's so cool!

104
00:04:09,470 --> 00:04:10,640
What should I do, Tie Chui?

105
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:14,100
I think I've found true love again.

106
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:16,050
I'm done. It's your turn.

107
00:04:19,310 --> 00:04:20,500
Hah,

108
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,650
I borrowed all of your poems

109
00:04:22,650 --> 00:04:24,290
from the Internet,

110
00:04:24,910 --> 00:04:26,740
and now that I read your poem
aloud before you,

111
00:04:26,990 --> 00:04:28,510
you have nothing to compete against me.

112
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:32,020
Brother Yue is such a great poet

113
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:33,700
for being able to write
such a beautiful poem.

114
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:35,430
I shouldn't embarrass myself
with my mediocre poem.

115
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,010
Let's go to the next round.

116
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:37,990
Fine!

117
00:04:38,710 --> 00:04:40,110
Then the theme of the second round

118
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,210
is about spring outing.

119
00:04:42,330 --> 00:04:42,820
How about that?

120
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:44,720
Spring outing?

121
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,360
Fine. Let's do that then.

122
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:49,410
I'll go first.

123
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:51,990
Look at the wooded ridges,
deep blue dappled with red.

124
00:04:52,170 --> 00:04:54,180
Look at the meadows,
an endless stretch of green.

125
00:04:54,430 --> 00:04:56,690
Look at the visitors trampling about
right in front of the pavilion,

126
00:04:56,690 --> 00:04:59,020
heedless of the fallen flowers
that betoken spring’s decline.

127
00:04:59,020 --> 00:05:00,150
This is the poem I gave him!

128
00:05:00,150 --> 00:05:01,940
What's going on?

129
00:05:02,090 --> 00:05:02,650
I'll pass this round.

130
00:05:02,850 --> 00:05:03,810
I have a great poem in my mind.

131
00:05:03,810 --> 00:05:04,450
Yes, I know.

132
00:05:04,570 --> 00:05:05,780
The twilight shines
on the Yangtze River,

133
00:05:05,780 --> 00:05:06,950
and we invite each other
to row back to the dock.

134
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:08,150
The falling flowers seem
to have affection,

135
00:05:08,150 --> 00:05:09,670
as it flows at the direction
of the boat.

136
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:11,620
Great!

137
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:12,890
Great!

138
00:05:16,580 --> 00:05:17,240
How do you...

139
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:18,520
How do I what?

140
00:05:19,150 --> 00:05:20,160
I spoke first.

141
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,410
There's no way I could've copied yours.

142
00:05:26,590 --> 00:05:27,510
You're a great poet.

143
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:30,010
I admit defeat. Goodbye.

144
00:05:35,540 --> 00:05:36,110
Ladies and gentlemen,

145
00:05:37,020 --> 00:05:39,400
it looks like we have a winner today.

146
00:05:40,020 --> 00:05:41,370
Mr. Yue, congratulations!

147
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,160
Thanks! Thanks!

148
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:46,500
Mr. Yue,

149
00:05:46,860 --> 00:05:47,950
